title: USC cancels all commencement speakers after canceled valedictorian speech
description: The University of Southern California announced on Friday all commencement speakers are being eliminated from the commencement ceremony next week.

title: Volkswagen workers in Tennessee have voted to join UAW, union says
description: 4,326 workers at the Volkswagen facility were eligible to vote.

title: New York AG asks court to reject Trump's $175M bond for civil judgment
description: Letitia James contended the former president failed to demonstrate that the company behind his bond had the resources to pay it if his appeal failed.

title: Man dies after setting himself on fire outside courthouse where Trump is on trial
description: The man, Maxwell Azzarello, was badly burned and taken to a hospital in critical condition, officials said, but he later died from his injuries.

title: 5 teens injured in shooting at senior skip day gathering in Maryland park: Police
description: Five teenagers were shot after gunfire rang out at a large gathering of high school students taking part in a senior skip day in Maryland, police said.

title: 10-year-old boy confesses to fatally shooting a man in his sleep 2 years ago, Texas authorities say
description: Authorities in Texas say a 10-year-old boy has confessed to an unsolved 2022 killing, telling investigators that he shot a man he did not know while the victim slept

title: An Alabama prison warden is arrested on drug charges
description: The warden of an Alabama prison was arrested Friday on drug charges

title: North Korea says it tested 'super-large' cruise missile warhead and new anti-aircraft missile
description: North Korea says it tested a “super-large” cruise missile warhead and a new anti-aircraft missile in a western coastal area as it expands its military capabilities in the face of deepening tensions with the United States and South Korea

title: Idaho group says it is exploring a ballot initiative for abortion rights and reproductive care
description: A new Idaho organization says it will ask voters to restore abortion access and other reproductive health care rights in the state after lawmakers let a second legislative session end without modifying the strict abortion bans

title: West Virginia will not face $465M COVID education funds clawback after feds OK waiver, governor says
description: West Virginia will not face a clawback of $465 million in COVID-19 money from the federal government, alleviating concerns raised by state lawmakers during the legislative session in March

title: House Democrats help Johnson avoid foreign aid bills defeat, despite GOP defections
description: The House on Friday cleared a key procedural hurdle in passing foreign aid to Israel, Ukraine and Taiwan, despite Republican defections.

title: 'American Idol' singer and Grammy winner Mandisa dies at 47
description: Mandisa, who competed on season 5 of "American Idol," has died, the singer's rep confirmed to ABC News.

title: 25 years later, Columbine survivors speak on the impact of the mass shooting
description: The tragic events at Columbine High School in 1999, when 12 students and one teacher died in a mass shooting, marked a turning point for America.

title: LIVE:  ABC News Live
description: 24/7 coverage of breaking news and live events

title: House to vote on foreign aid bills for Ukraine, Israel
description: The House will vote Saturday on foreign aid bills to provide assistance to Ukraine, Israel and Taiwan.

title: WATCH:  TSA explosives detection canine given party to celebrate retirement
description: Messi, the TSA explosives detection canine, had a retirement party in Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport complete with over a dozen tennis balls, a bubble machine, party hat and cupcake.

title: WATCH:  Watch the moment this dog patiently introduces himself to his new puppy brother
description: The most gentle doggy introduction you’ll ever see.

title: WATCH:  Tourists flock to see Death Valley in bloom
description: Gorgeous fields of wildflowers are taking over California with bright yellow daisies even popping up in Death Valley, the driest and hottest place in America.

title: WATCH:  Watch this dog that can solve math problems with her paw
description: Luna, a mini cockapoo, has a unique talent for solving math problems with help from her owner.

title: WATCH:  Taylor Swift fans count down to release of ‘The Tortured Poets Department’
description: In true Taylor Swift fashion, Easter eggs abound as the megastar drops clues about Friday’s release of her new studio album.

title: WATCH:  353 ballerinas broke the world record for dancing on pointe in one place
description: Hundreds of young dancers gathered in New York's Plaza Hotel on Wednesday to break the world record for dancing on pointe in one place.

title: WATCH:  Cat rescued from Dubai flooding after clinging to car door
description: A cat clinging to a car door was rescued by police in Dubai after two years' worth of rain fell in just 24 hours.

title: WATCH:  Escaped circus elephant stops traffic in Montana
description: A circus elephant got loose and roamed through traffic in Butte, Montana, on Tuesday. It was returned safely by its handlers.

title: WATCH:  Dubai hit with severe flooding
description: Dubai was hit with severe flooding on Tuesday after two years' worth of rain fell in just 24 hours, records show.

title: WATCH:  3 shih tzus pop their heads up above a tub mid-bath
description: Mabel, Alice, and August were ready for bath time to be over.
